Southern Company Reports Fourth Quarter and Full 2016 Earnings 



ATLANTA, Feb. 22, 2017 /PRNewswire/ – Southern Company today reported fourth-quarter 2016 earnings of $197 million, or 20 cents per share, compared with earnings of $271 million, or 30 cents per share, in the fourth quarter of 2015.  Southern Company also reported full year 2016 earnings of $2.45 billion, or $2.57 per share, compared with earnings of $2.37 billion, or $2.60 per share, for the same period in 2015.







